# 1. All the packages you need to install
First clone the repository
Then cd into P3/backend and setup the virtual env and activate it
Make sure you have python and pip installed
Then simply run the following commands
pip install django Pillow djangorestframework djangorestframework-simplejwt django-cors-headers
python3 manage.py makemigrations
python3 manage.py migrate
python3 manage.py loaddata final.json
python3 manage.py runserver
then in another terminal, cd into P3/frontend/petpal and run the commands
npm ci
npm start
and you can start browsing!!
